-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ch_film
  Film graph included with Chaco distribution.
  Small finite element grid with quadrilateral elements.
  Graph and coordinates included.
  No vertex weights.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Answers differ for ParMETIS tests on linux platforms 
Suspect difference in rand() is the cause.
On linux, rand() returns values in the range 0 to 2147483647; on
Solaris, it returns values in the range 0 to 32767.  (See definition of
RAND_MAX in <stdlib.h>.)

- zdrive.inp.rcb-partlocal1:  Answer differ between linux and sun due to
roundoff in computation of targethi in par_median.c.  On linux, the "upper
too small" test is satisfied (due to roundoff) in a case for which it is not
satisfied (i.e., Goldilocks condition is satisfied) on the sun.  Thus, an
extra point is shifted in linux, changing the subdomain shapes and resulting
cut directions for subsequent cuts.  This problem goes away when compilation
flag -g is used instead of -O for linux.
